  "instructions": [
    "Heat the lardons in a large skillet over medium-high heat until browned, about 5 minutes. ",
    "Add the pork shoulder to the skillet and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes. ",
    "Add the gochujang, soy sauce, rice vinegar, garlic, and ginger to the skillet and stir to combine. ",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 5-7 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through. ",
    "Stir in the cream of tartar, sugar, and black pepper. ",
    "Reduce heat to medium-low and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes. ",
    "Season with sesame oil and serve hot, garnished with green onions. ",
    "Serve with a side of rice and kimchi, if desired."
  ],
